<p><strong>Sydney, {{ date | readableDate }}</strong> • OneQode is pleased to announce its partnership with <a href="https://letsplay.live/" rel="noopener">LetsPlay.Live</a> (LPL), one of the world's most established esports and gaming content broadcasters.</p>
<p>The partnership kicks off by delivering a major Counter-Strike 2 esports project for the Asia-Pacific (APAC) region: <a href="https://gg.letsplay.live/tournament/frontier-grassroots-cs2-brought-to-you-by-lpl-powered-by-oneqode-6549a91db4ea445f26a1acdd?tabs=overview&amp;utm_source=PressRelease&amp;utm_medium=OneQodePR&amp;utm_campaign=OneQodeFrontier&amp;utm_id=LPLMarketing" rel="noopener">OneQode Frontier Grassroots presented by LetsPlay.Live</a>. The tournament is open to Counter-Strike players aged 16 years and over located in APAC, including Oceania, South-East Asia, and the Pacific Islands. Players will compete for a share of a USD $6,000 prize pool.</p>
<p>The upcoming competition will be hosted on both the LetsPlay.Live website and OneQode’s platform, leveraging both OneQode’s latency-optimized Asia-Pacific-wide digital infrastructure, and LPL’s expertise in producing and delivering quality live esports events.</p>
<p>OneQode Frontier Grassroots stands to be one of the first tournaments available to teams in Asia-Pacific for Counter-Strike 2: the latest instalment in the widely popular Counter-Strike video game franchise.</p>
